<TITLE> BURIGANGA DUMPING 5 OCs face contempt, appear on Wed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com)-- The High Court on Monday issued a contempt of court rule against five officers in charge of Dhaka police stations for not complying with a previous order to stop dumping of waste onto the bank of the river Buriganga. It ordered Kotwali police chief Salahuddin Khan, Hajaribagh police chief Enamul Haque, Lalbagh police chief Mohammad Ali, Kamrangirchar police chief Shafiqul Islam and Demra police chief Mahbub Hossain to appear in person before the court on Wednesday. The bench of justices Mohammad Momtazuddin Ahmed and Naima Haider gave the order on a petition filed by human rights organisation Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh. The court also asked them to explain why punitive measure should not be taken against them for disobeying the court order. The High Court on May 4 asked authorities to deploy police at the Buriganga banks to stop the dumping of waste. But the police officials did not make the deployment. Manzil Morshed argued for the petitioner. Deputy attorney general Mostafa Zaman Islam represented the state bdnews2
